{
    int x { 5 };

    std::cout << x; // variable now used somewhere

    return 0;
}But this requires some effort to write code that uses it, and has the downside of potentially changing your program’s behavior.The[[maybe_unused]]attributeC++17In some cases, neither of the above options are desirable. Consider the case where we have a set of math/physics values that we use in many different programs:#include <iostream>

